content:
 1/2 to 1 cup icing sugar 250 gr. Pkg cream cheese 1 envelope Dream Whip or 1 cup whipping cream 1 tin cherry pie filling 1 graham crumb crust Bake crumb crust at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Cream cheese and sugar till nice and soft. Make Dream Whip and combine with cheese. Cover graham crust. Put cherries on top. Leave in refrigerator for 24 hours.
CRUST;
Ingredients ¼ cup melted butter 4 tbsp white sugar 1-1/4 cup graham crumbs Instructions Combine and press in 9”x 9” pan.

WHITE SAUCE;
1 cup milk 4 tbsp flour Cook as for white sauce, and let cool.
BEAT WELL;
Ingredients 1 cup butter or margarine 1 cup white sugar 1 tsp vanilla. Instructions When sauce is cooled, add the butter and sugar mixture, and BEAT WELL.
Makes enough for a layer cake.
